race.comment: The feature of the day here and PLAYIN'IT SWEET (1) looks the one to beat after a strong performance in the Breeders' Classic last time out. Out in trip here isn't an issue and she has the speed to get across from the tricky gate. May be able to go to another level out in trip now and that's a bad sign for her rivals. LINCHPIN (5) stuck on well in the Breeders' behind PLAYIN'IT SWEET and he'll be better for that effort. He returned with a new peak there and has a stack of upside. Can continue to rise through the grades and he looks a big player. DOMINATUS (2) is an exciting horse on resumption after two wins prior to the break. He looked very smooth in his recent trial win and this trip first-up looks ideal. Pike sticks with him and he can pick up from where he left off. ABERDEEN FLYER (3) can improve on the first-up effort despite the wide draw. ADMIRE ASTRA (10) draws an inside barrier here and she's not to be discounted despite being up in grade here.
